body_html:
Yeah, it's not Xcode, as you're still on the step before you can use Xcode (building the libraries).

Did you maybe misinterpret the deleted lines as empty lines?

It needs to look like this:

lipo \
${LIBDIR}/iossim_386/lib/libprotobuf-lite.a \
${LIBDIR}/ios_arm7/lib/libprotobuf-lite.a \
${LIBDIR}/ios_arm7s/lib/libprotobuf-lite.a \
${LIBDIR}/ios_arm64/lib/libprotobuf-lite.a \
-create \
-output ${LIBDIR}/libprotobuf-lite.a

not

lipo \
${LIBDIR}/iossim_386/lib/libprotobuf-lite.a \

${LIBDIR}/ios_arm7/lib/libprotobuf-lite.a \
${LIBDIR}/ios_arm7s/lib/libprotobuf-lite.a \
${LIBDIR}/ios_arm64/lib/libprotobuf-lite.a \
-create \
-output ${LIBDIR}/libprotobuf-lite.a

Or else, maybe did you remove one of those trailing backslashes?

From your error logs, I can tell that you are running the command:

+ lipo /Users/kduy/temp/tensorflow/tensorflow/contrib/makefile/gen/protobuf_ios/lib/iossim_386/lib/libprotobuf.a

which means that the second half of the command is getting cut off.

body:
Yeah, it's not Xcode, as you're still on the step before you can use Xcode (building the libraries).

Did you maybe misinterpret the deleted lines as empty lines?

It needs to look like this:

```
lipo \
${LIBDIR}/iossim_386/lib/libprotobuf-lite.a \
${LIBDIR}/ios_arm7/lib/libprotobuf-lite.a \
${LIBDIR}/ios_arm7s/lib/libprotobuf-lite.a \
${LIBDIR}/ios_arm64/lib/libprotobuf-lite.a \
-create \
-output ${LIBDIR}/libprotobuf-lite.a
```

not

```
lipo \
${LIBDIR}/iossim_386/lib/libprotobuf-lite.a \

${LIBDIR}/ios_arm7/lib/libprotobuf-lite.a \
${LIBDIR}/ios_arm7s/lib/libprotobuf-lite.a \
${LIBDIR}/ios_arm64/lib/libprotobuf-lite.a \
-create \
-output ${LIBDIR}/libprotobuf-lite.a
```

Or else, maybe did you remove one of those trailing backslashes?

From your error logs, I can tell that you are running the command:

```
+ lipo /Users/kduy/temp/tensorflow/tensorflow/contrib/makefile/gen/protobuf_ios/lib/iossim_386/lib/libprotobuf.a
```

which means that the second half of the command is getting cut off.
